OL,3,CHunt 'would like to' cut taxes before
OL,4,Celection if it can be done
OL,5,C'responsibly'
OL,7,FQuestioned by ITV News Business and
OL,8,FEconomics Editor Joel Hills on
OL,9,FWednesday over whether he will try to
OL,10,Fcut taxes before the next election, Mr
OL,11,FHunt said he "wants to bring down the
OL,12,Ftax burden" despite calls to
OL,13,Fprioritise funding for public services.
OL,15,FHe described it as a "central divide
OL,16,Fin British politics" and added: "A
OL,17,FLabour Party that is basically happy
OL,18,Fwith the tax burden as it is, and a
OL,19,FConservative party that says no, if we
OL,20,Fwant to be competitive and successful,
OL,21,Fwe need to bring down taxes."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
